##"I am a refugee" , she bought on behalf of anti-epidemic materials for the name of fraud million arrested

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

By Zhu Yiyi, thepaper.cn

"Do you know why you're being arrested? "

"Yes. "

"Home is in Yangpu District. How did you get here (Baoshan District) ! "

"I'VE COME TO ESCAPE! "

The conversation between the police and the suspect took place at the scene of the arrest. On February 25, police in Yangpu District, Shanghai, arrested Zhou, a suspect in a telecommunications network fraud, for selling anti-plague products, in a rented house in Luodian, Baoshan District. When the police caught Zhou, its own absconding as "escape. ".

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
This photo was provided by Shanghai police

Reporter of the paper news (www.thepaper.cn ) learned from the Yangpu District police in Shanghai that at around 1:00 on February 23, a resident surnamed Chen reported to the Yangpu District police that he was swindled out of 150,000 yuan in the process of buying a body heat gun online. After receiving the report, under the guidance of the criminal investigation team of the Municipal Public Security Bureau, the Criminal Investigation detachment of the Yangpu District Public Security Bureau will conduct an investigation together with the Siping Road police station.

Police arrested a suspected criminal surnamed Zhou on Feb. 25 in a rented house in Luodian, Baoshan District, Shanghai. Zhou described his escape as "fleeing" . Video source, Shanghai Police, editing, Zeng Yinzi 00:35

Originally, the company of Chen Mou wants to resume work recently. As a result of epidemic prevention work needs, urgently needs to purchase a batch of body temperature guns. During this period, Chen introduced through a friend, met a woman Zhou, Zhou said there are channels to buy masks, body temperature gun and other anti-epidemic supplies. Due to the introduction of a friend, Chen soon and Zhou negotiated a unit price of 300 yuan to buy a total of 500 body temperature gun.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Screenshot via Wechat

At the same time, at the request of the other side, Chen through the network transfer of 150,000 yuan to Zhou.

Since then, Chen repeatedly urged Zhou delivery, but Zhou has been prevaricating with various reasons. Until the agreed final delivery date, Chan Mou found that Zhou's mobile phone is turned off, no longer contact, found cheated, and reported to the police.

Investigators found through the visit, since February 2020, Zhou in wechat friends often posted masks, disinfection water, temperature gun and other types of anti-epidemic supplies advertising, and many times to the surrounding friends, former colleagues to solicit business. In fact, she did not sell the relevant epidemic prevention supplies qualifications and channels. Just before the so-called final delivery date he promised, Zhou left his Yangpu District home in a hurry and disappeared.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Fake Id

The police then expanded the scope of their investigation. After days of tracing, he was finally found to have absconded to Luodian, Baoshan District. At noon on February 25, after waiting for an ambush, investigators in a local rental house will be arrested.

After the case, Zhou truthfully confessed to sell anti-epidemic supplies for the name of swindling others money and property of the criminal facts. According to Zhou, it had previously engaged in the network Daigou. Because recently found that there are many people on the Internet to buy face masks, body temperature gun and other anti-epidemic supplies, its will use a twisted mind, in the knowledge that they do not have the relevant qualifications and channels, to buy on behalf of the sale of these anti-epidemic materials to commit fraud. After verification, since February 2020, his five crimes, the value of more than 1 million yuan.

The police reminds: buys the mask, the body temperature gun and so on epidemic prevention supplies must pass the regular channel, does not believe others to transfer the remittance creditably. If the operator is found to have engaged in illegal acts such as selling counterfeit or substandard products or committing fraud, he may report the matter to the nearest Public Security Bureau.
